{"word":"καταέννυμι","slug":"καταέννυμι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταέννυμι</b></el> <el>(or <el>-εινύω</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>, aor1 and <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a>\n<p/><i>to clothe, cover</i>, <el>θριξὶ νέκυν καταείνυσαν</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ὄρος καταειμένον ὕλῃ</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/>"}]}